ucpp
------------------------------------------
A C preprocessor is a part of a C compiler responsible for macro replacement,
conditional compilation and inclusion of header files. It is often found as a
stand-alone program on Unix systems.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libucpp-devel-1.3.5-1bl1
  libucpp13-1.3.5-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.3.0-3
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://gitlab.com/scarabeusiv/ucpp

Canonical download:
  https://gitlab.com/scarabeusiv/ucpp/-/archive/1.3.5/ucpp-1.3.5.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ucpp-1.3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ucpp-1.3.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ucpp-1.3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ucpp-1.3.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libucpp13-1.3.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libucpp-devel-1.3.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ucpp)
  /usr/bin/ucpp.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ucpp.README
  /usr/share/doc/ucpp/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/ucpp/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/ucpp/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/ucpp.1.gz

(libucpp13)
  /usr/bin/cygucpp-13.dll

(libucpp-devel)
  /usr/include/libucpp/cpp.h
  /usr/include/libucpp/hash.h
  /usr/include/libucpp/mem.h
  /usr/include/libucpp/nhash.h
  /usr/include/libucpp/tune.h
  /usr/include/libucpp/ucpp-config.h
  /usr/include/libucpp/ucppi.h
  /usr/lib/libucpp.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libucpp.pc

